SampleNumber: Order in which samples were collected, per bucket
FLWC Detail: Food and landscape waste compost (FLWC) sample detail
FLWC Age Months: Food and landscape waste compost (FLWC) age in months
FLWC Location: Food and landscape waste compost (FLWC) Source location
Sampler Initials: Study author or anonymous study participant who performed sample collection.
Bulking Material Detail: Description of bulking material used in composting toilet
Composting Time Point: Time point (TP) at which the human excrement sample was collected, analogous to the week of composting.
Crate Location: Location in storage crate at time of sample collection
Temp Top Bucket C: Temperature (C) at top of bucket at time of sample collection
Temp Bottom Bucket C: Temperature (C) at bottom of bucket at time of sample collection
Average Ambient Temp: Mean of Temp Top Bucket and Temp Bottom Bucket
Observations Outside Bucket: Text description of observations related to outside of composting bucket collected during sampling
Observations Vent Tube: Text description of observations when looking at venting tube of composting bucket collected during sampling. When multiple descriptions are presented, the most prominent observations are first.
Visible Contents Access Port: Text description of observations when looking through access port of composting bucket collected during sampling. When multiple descriptions are presented, the most prominent observations are first.
Compost Temp C: Temperature (C) of compost at time of sampling.
Compost Moisture Percent: Moisture content as measured with Vegetronix Soil Moisture probe. This device often malfunctioned resulting in many missing values here.
Observed Sample Color: Sample color, as determined by manual comparison to color swatches. Y: yellow; LY: light yellow; LB: light brown; MB: medium brown; DB: dark brown; BL: black.
Observed Sample Moisture: Percieved sample moisture. L: low; M: medium; H: high; SAT: saturated
Observed Sample Contents: Text description of observations of collected sample material. When multiple descriptions are presented, the most prominent observations are first.
Observed Sample Smell: Percieved odors collected by wafting from the sample. When multiple descriptions are presented, the most prominent observations are first.
Observed Sample Organisms YN: Presence (Y) or absence (N) of visible organisms in collected samples.
sample-uuid: UUID for sample, as generated with cual-id.
